Have you got a file called `MG_2158.CR2` and another called `img_2158.cr2` would be the first thing to check?  Amazon cloud drive can't have files which differ only in case.

If it does that every time you sync then that is probably the explanation.  If not then retrying the sync will probably clear it up.

Hello Nick, thank you for responding my question.

I retry this same backup today to see if I pass errors but I have no good news to tell you. These are the errors.
Have you any idea for me?
Best regards,
David.

I haven't seen `Next token is expired` errors before.  Does the listing take a really long time?

Worth trying at a different time of day.

Did you see about that duplicate file?

Thanks

Nick

> Does the listing take a really long time?

Well, it is less than 13 minutes. I guess it is because of some server restarts/reconfiguration going on at Amazon.

The failure is in `func (s *NodesService) listNodes`, but it doesn't do anything else than reading nodes. Concurrent reads are limited by the pacer, so we don't do limit the client in any fashion.

Are you by any chance running multiple simultaneous uploads?

I don't know if writes from another client will invalidate the tokens. Depends on Amazon.

Fortunately, the error "next token is expired" was only that day and today is not present. Less bad.

Responding to your question Nick. Yes, I have many jpg images with same file name, but in different folders. But I haven't two images with same file name in same folder. Every folder in this usb hd drive is a compact flash card copied from the camera. The camera assign filenames to the images in every card with IMGxxxxx.jpg from 1 to 9999, so you can see sometimes same filename but always in different folders. 

Let me give you some more extra information. I uploaded the first backup of this usb drive (1.5TB), using the official amazon desktop application, and now I am trying to use rclone to uploading just the new files. At the moment I haven't added new files to the usb drive, so now there are the same files in my local usb drive than in acd.

Could you fix rclone to admit having the same filename in different folders on ACD?, or do you think that Amazon doesn't admit it?. If you think the last option, It is extrange for me see that I was able to upload the entire usb using official acd desktop app without errors.

Let's see... Kind regards and thank you for your interest in this issue
David

>  same filename in different folders on ACD

This shouldn't be a problem.

I think the problem might just have been temporary - does the sync work properly now?

Sounds to me like https://github.com/ncw/rclone/issues/263. I'm guessing the directory you're uploading contains a lot of files?

Amazon Cloud Drive has been finicky for the past month or so, and it seems to be mostly Amazon's fault. The sync should eventually work; it depends on the day.

No, it continues giving error in same point. I have tried rclone copy for the full hard disk drive another 4 days more and always gives me the same errors with it reaches this folder:
- boda laura y oscar/foto/1/DCIM/100EOS5D/

To discard problems over this folder, I have tried rclone copy for this folder only and it worked well without errors.

Tested again just now and continues giving same error.

lines of error here:
http://pastebin.com/b8bbDccd

It could be any database used by rclone or any configuration file used for rclone to annotate what things to do in this backup, corrupted or broken?. If yes, is there any way to clean or recreate this cache, db or config file in rclone?.

@bunset thank you that log is very useful.

I can see the "Next token is expired" messages.  It is clear to me that these are the cause of the "409 Conflict" messages - rclone didn't read part of the directory listing, so missed out some files.

It would be fairly easy to change the recursion strategy for listing from depth first into width first - that should fix the token expired messages hopefully.

Also I'm concerned that the error in the listing didn't seem to get passed up to the master sync command - it really should have done.

Also rclone spends ages retrying those 409 Conflicts for no gain.

I'm also getting this 409 Conflict (NAME_ALREADY_EXISTS) error. Trying to copy 250GB folder with photos. My camera rolled over its file name counter several times so there a duplicities but never in the same folder. Below is a link to verbose logs and a list of all photos I back up. Each time I run rclone the error appears on different directory and file. I still need to upload most of the photos but the copy get so slow with the 409 error and retries that it would be impossible to finish in reasonable time. I run rclone v1.26 on Synology NAS. First time I ran rclone I managed to copy 100GB of photos without any error. Then we had power outage and since then I encounter this error.

logs and file list of local photo directory
https://www.dropbox.com/sh/8rk42habdvtaf8h/AAC6xdXArxZAtQNrWBhYJ6JCa?dl=0

Hi Nick. Thank you for reviewing the errors. 
Let me know if there is anything else I can help you until you can fix it, for example if you need remote connection to my desktop computer to see these errors or debugging them while they are happening. Just tell me.

Thanks and Kind regards!
David
